parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle can cause loss of control, accidents, and fatalities.
symptoms: Loud noises
vibrations
and difficulty steering; rear axle fractures or cracks
causing the vehicle to shift or drop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the front subframe can cause loss of control, accidents, and fatalities.
symptoms: Rust holes
corrosion
or fractures in the front subframe
causing the vehicle to become unstable or collapse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Suspension issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and fatalities.
symptoms: Wandering or pulling to one side
loud noises
vibrations
and difficulty steering; corrosion or fractures in the rear lower trailing arms
coil springs
or other suspension components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and fatalities.
symptoms: Difficulty steering
loud noises
vibrations
and pulling to one side; corrosion or fractures in the steering components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle won't shift into gear
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle's speedometer or odometer malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear axle failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear axle fractures or breaks
the vehicle sways or wobbles
the vehicle makes unusual noises
the vehicle's speedometer or odometer malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and shifter column failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the shifter column fails to engage
the vehicle won't shift into gear
the vehicle's speedometer or odometer malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle rolling in park can cause accidents or injuries, especially if the vehicle is on an incline or in a crowded area.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls or moves while in park
the vehicle's parking pawl fails to engage
the vehicle's transmission or gear system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ejection of spark plugs can cause the engine to misfire, leading to loss of power, rough idling, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The spark plug blows out of the engine
causing a loud noise
rough running
and loss of power. The engine may also produce white smoke or a burning odor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The alternator fails
causing the vehicle to stall or catch fire. There may be a burning odor or smoke coming from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The electrical system fails
causing the vehicle to stall or catch fire. There may be a burning odor or smoke coming from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intake manifold failure can cause the engine to run poorly, leading to loss of power and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The intake manifold fails
causing the engine to run poorly and lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls
often while driving
causing loss of power and potentially leading to accidents.
